DATA CLOUD
Preferred Attribute Name

To control activation field names, use preferred attribute names in Data Cloud. When you include additional attributes in an activation, you can give the attribute a preferred name for that activation. Audiences activated to Marketing Cloud Engagement include the preferred attribute name field so you can use them in your existing content personalization scripts. Preferred names don't carry over to the next activation using the same attribute. Preferred names must be set up in each activation.

The preferred name must be unique in the activation definition. For example, you can’t have two attributes with the same preferred name when configuring an activation. When activating to Engagement, the preferred name can’t include these characters: ! @ # $ % ^ * ( ) = { } [ ] \ . < > / " : ? | , _ &.
